rom this comparison—they're independent from the baseline. So I'm checking: did any of the originally tracked sessions change status or die? No. Did any new sessions that should be tracked appear? Looking at the child sessions, the planner and master-orchestrator subagents are all showing as done, which matches what I'd expect from the baseline.\\n\\nNow I'm reviewing the current state across all the active sessions. The cron jobs are all running as expected—the QLHV monitor, DTLX monitor, and agent status check are all stable. The telegram group is also running but hasn't had activity in about 17 minutes, which is a bit stale but not alarming. The main session ended around 20 minutes ago, which is fine since it was just a heartbeat check. So everything looks healthy and consistent with the baseline—no changes to report.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Silent. All critical sessions remain stable vs. stored baseline (20:29 UTC):\\n\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ running (QLHV 5p — ~97m, expected long-running)\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ running (DTLX 5p — stable)\\n- `cron:e7885813` ✅ running (Agent Status — stable)\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅ running (stale ~17m, known)\\n- `main` ✅ done (ended ~19:28 UTC — expected)\\n- All child subagents: done (confirmed clean)\\n\\nNo failures. No blockers. Pipeline: HEALTHY.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 29375,\n            \"output\": 1003,\n            \"totalTokens\": 44745,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 423,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776201170978,\n          \"responseId\": \"062de0d474380201890ba5a0df6191cd\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n    