{"type":"message","id":"5154cb3f","parentId":"ea691579","timestamp":"2026-04-14T21:15:26.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session timed out, which means it's in a waiting state. Let me check the session status to understand what happened. Actually, the session timed out because there might not be anyone to respond (the user is not in the session). Let me try again or check the session status.\n\nActually the session_send timed out, which means it tried to send and wait for a response. But this is a one-way notification to Lead, so I don't need to wait for a response. Let me just note that the delivery had a timeout but was likely sent (it just didn't get a response back).\n\nActually, `sessions_send` with `timeoutSeconds` default will wait for the target session to respond. \n\nSince Lead's Telegram direct session is probably idle, I should just try sending again with a zero timeout to send it without waiting for a response.","thinkingSignature":"c3e7bcbc352fc06eced754231788d73e8b2e326154bcffdba57ab1c46c646da7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3pb4jjs0psdo_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 21:14 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:ed2d0b5d: running — 5p Progress Report (QLHV) — ~59m\n• cron:6f3323ef: running — 5p Progress Report (DTLX) — ~26m\n• cron:e7885813: running — Agent Status to Lead — ~1m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258: running — QLHV group session — ~4h45m (stale ~27m)\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: none\n\n— Orbis 🌐","timeoutSeconds":0}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":180,"output":384,"cacheRead":14084,"cacheWrite":25924,"totalTokens":40572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776201317134,"responseId":"062de166586be